Dialogue: My only thought is, I like Gil. People like Gil. He’s great. I just have
this sneaking feeling if he won an election he might quite like to line
up me and everyone I know, and shoot us?
What? What is it?
I think it’s actually brave to go.
And, I know he spoke abominably to you. So just for context, would it
be appropriate this weekend, in a bridge-building way, for me to be
speaking to Logan or no?
Got it, sure. Because I want to have your back. But there’s also my
back. We’re a beast with two backs.
No, of course, I know that.
Oh. Great. Great that he can get a, a bit of time away from the masses.
Is he okay? He’s not dead?
No. Great. No. It’s only because, he’s one of those people where I
would be like, no! But also, yeah?
He hasn’t fallen off the wagon has he?
Here he is, man of the people … who work on his ranch!
Wow!
Yee-haw. I have never ridden a horse. Can you believe it?
Well, I think Shiv’s position would be that she has nothing to say
sorry for?
I think obviously—
She’s sad about the way things happened? We could offer that?
Okay. I did it.
I blanked your dad.
Can I—?
Oh? Right. Did you?
The pressure on the faucet is moderately intense so go easy.
Hey! It’ll be okay. You want me to come with you, into the emotional
swamp? Cos soon I’m gonna be part of this whole genetic carnival.
For better or worse. Haha!
It’s like waving your kids off to school.
Shall I be mother?
All girls together!
Do you think they’re talking about us?
This is a lovely place, Willa. Are you here often?
That old biological clock starts a-ticking! You can always freeze?
I’d like Shiv to freeze. Embryos not eggs. Little bit of me in the bank!
Have you thought of that?
So?? C’mon.
What did everyone say!
Nothing too horrible? Or upsetting? Or just disgusting?
Oh. So it’s all, resolved?
Sure. But listen. You’re okay right? Sometimes I don’t know.
If it helps to make up numbers I’d be pleased to … get involved.
I feel I should apologize. For blanking you earlier. Clear the air.
Ignoring you.
I’m sure it wasn’t clear but I try to hold myself to a higher standard—
when it comes to inter-family turmoil and etiquette and—
Hey!
He knocked his teeth out in the pool.
Maybe we should chat this over in the morning?
It is her job?
Honey. You don’t need to apologize. I know it’s not true.
